 It is not clear what led to the strike. Residents who arrived at about 07:00 were left with no choice but to leave as the employees locked themselves inside the building. When www.mobserver.co.za arrived at the offices at about 09:00, it found frustrated residents waiting outside the building hoping to be assisted.
Minutes later an employee told the angry residents to enter the building to receive assistance. He told www.mobserver.co.za that only three out of 18 workers were willing to work, he further said that the other colleagues had left work and were nowhere to be found.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za